<br>
Actually it isn't. This board was created sometime spring 1999 by Kayla, guildmistress of Eye of the Ages (I'm sure the old schoolers remember EotA). As time passed Kayla made a few other Nameless players board admins. In december 99 she left Nameless and started a new guild on Vazaelle and never came back, she left this board behind (didn't moderate/maintain it anyway for quite some time before she left). I didn't follow NT close enough to know in detail what happened but apparently the board admins promoted other people of their choice to board admins and so on. No idea who's an admin today.<br>
<br>
If Kayla came back to this board today she would have the power to shut it down, delete everything, take away admin access etc., whatever pleases her.<br>
<br>
Point of this post is? Not sure, just stating a few facts (at least I hope I remembered it all right).<br>
<br>
No the admins have not been elected, no they have not created this board, no it's not theirs. Yes, they (at least Barnabuss) have put in a lot of time and deserve credit for it. Should they be allowed to act like dictators? No. Can we do anything against that? Not really, if you're not happy with how they treat you, don't come here.<br>
